r-performing-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Blur-performing-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Blur-performing-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Blur-performing-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="/artists/blur">Blur</a>分享了他们最新专辑《 <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/blur-the-ballad-of-darren-review-lyrics-tracklist-3470424">The Ballad Of Darren</a> 》中一首未发行的新曲目《Sticks And Stones》。</p><ul class="post-content-read-more"><li><strong>阅读更多：<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/blur/page/2">模糊：每张专辑按伟大程度排名</a></strong></li></ul><p>这首歌曲是继乐队的另外两首歌曲<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/listen-to-two-new-blur-songs-the-rabbi-and-the-swan-3472648">《The Rabbi》和《The Swan》之后发行的，它们是作为专辑豪华版的一部分发行的</a>。 &#39;Sticks And Stones&#39; will be released as a bonus track for the Japanese exclusive edition of &#39;The Ballad Of Darren&#39;.</p><p> Guitarist Graham Coxon provides lead vocals on the track. The song features a mid-tempo beat with a psychedelic feel. <em>“It&#39;s written over my face / No sleep zone / Open up my suitcase / Sticks and stones”</em> sings Coxon during the songs chorus. </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="Sticks and Stones" width="696" height="522" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/OM3InrhYQtI?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> &#39;The Ballad Of Darren&#39; arrived on Friday, July 21. In <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/blur-the-ballad-of-darren-review-lyrics-tracklist-3470424">a four-star review of the album,</a> <em>NME</em> shared: “There&#39;s always a sense of unfinished business with Blur; they&#39;ve never officially split, but each time they re-emerge it&#39;s as if we&#39;re rekindling a long-estranged affair. Two albums in 20 years since 2003&#39;s &#39;Think Tank&#39; – &#39;The Ballad of Darren&#39; and 2015&#39;s <a href="https://www.nme.com/blogs/nme-blogs/blurs-new-album-the-magic-whip-worth-the-wait-first-listen-review-759374">&#39;The Magic Whip&#39;</a> – would suggest they feel the same.”</p><p> It continued: “On &#39;The Ballad…&#39; the band are muted and contemplative; there are moments of sheer heartbreak in these songs. Beyond the doom, there&#39;s something resolute and life-affirming in the way this record plays out; you sense the whole momentum of the band moving as a unit, not just pieced together in separate takes like in &#39;The Magic Whip&#39;.”</p><p> Blur recently headlined Øya 2023. In a <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/live/oya-2023-blur-boygenius-sigrid-review-photos-3483075">four-star review of the festival</a> , <em>NME</em> shared: “Now well into their reunion run for stellar 2023 comeback album &#39;The Ballad Of Darren&#39;, the Britpop heroes are a well-oiled machine running on boisterous festival fuel and artfully selected sideways moves.</p><p> “There&#39;s a grit to newbie &#39;St Charles Square&#39; that sits so perfectly alongside &#39;There&#39;s No Other Way&#39; and &#39;Popscene&#39;, with the band gleefully in the knowledge that they&#39;re in the finest of fettle. Even &#39;Trimm Trabb&#39; lands like a <em>FIFA</em> Soundtrack classic.” </p><figure id="attachment_3478546" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3478546" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3478546" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023_blur_damonalbarn_getty_2000x1270.jpg" alt="Blur's Damon Albarn" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023_blur_damonalbarn_getty_2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023_blur_damonalbarn_getty_2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023_blur_damonalbarn_getty_2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023_blur_damonalbarn_getty_2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023_blur_damonalbarn_getty_2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023_blur_damonalbarn_getty_2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3478546" class="wp-caption-text"> Blur&#39;s Damon Albarn at Lucca Summer Festival in Lucca CREDIT: Mairo Cinquetti/SOPA Images/LightRocket via Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p> In other news, the band&#39;s frontman, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/blurs-damon-albarn-says-were-gonna-need-more-drugs-to-get-through-absurd-ai-3478542">Damon Albarn recently addressed AI, branding it “absurd”</a> .</p><p> Albarn told <a href="https://www.thesun.co.uk/tvandshowbiz/23333817/iggy-azalea-new-album-onlyfans/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>The Sun</em></a> : “It&#39;s absurd. Anyone who has so much time to sing songs through a Michael Buble filter and put them on the internet is a fucking idiot. If the AIs are the future of music, we&#39;re gonna need better drugs to get us through it.”</p><p> Blur&#39;s bassist, Alex James recently <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/blur-alex-james-has-launched-a-new-britpop-sparkling-wine-3477705">launched his own brand of &#39;Britpop&#39; sparkling wine</a> .</p><p> The sparkling wine – labelled as &#39;Britpop Brut by Alex James&#39; – is available on August 12 exclusively to Laithwaites, and is priced at £25 per bottle. It is also listed as a dry, chardonnay-based blend made in the UK.</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/listen-to-new-unreleased-blur-song-sticks-and-stones-3486078">Listen to new, unreleased Blur song &#39;Sticks And Stones&#39;</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
